          About the role
         Trulia was founded in 2005 with the simple idea of making it easier for people to find a home. Today, this remains the core mission of the company, inspiring us to solve big problems and do great work. Trulia is an important part of Zillow Group, which houses a portfolio of the largest and most dynamic real estate and home-related brands.
         Trulia’s unique position within Zillow Group provides advantages for engineers who want to make a huge impact. We operate like a start-up within a large organization, with the mandate to innovate and build cool, consumer-facing products, while enjoying the benefits and resources that Zillow Group offers. Our engineers are allowed to focus on building products that make it easy and enjoyable place to live, for millions of people.
          About the team
         We are looking for a hands-on data scientist to work with our team of passionate and innovative engineers to integrate intelligence into the search platform and local services behind our real estate site and mobile apps. This role will involve close collaboration with engineering and product development. You'll work with a wide range of large-scale data related to properties and local info, at the core of consumer-facing products and the Trulia experience.
         Trulia’s culture is one of the company’s biggest strengths. At Trulia people treat each other with respect and compassion, together cultivating a culture of collaboration, learning, accountability and fun. There’s a dedication to understanding the whole person, helping to build a collegian, trusting environment.
         Who you are?
          Problem solver, beyond algorithms and data structures
          Strong background or experience in information retrieval, data mining, machine learning or statistics
          Adept in data analysis, able to synthesize and interpret metrics, perform both recurring and ad hoc analyses, and present findings to cross-functional key partners
          Proficient in Java and/or Scala or Python
          Industry experience in search ranking/relevance or data science
          Exposure to Hadoop, MapReduce, Spark or other Big Data platforms
         What Would Get Our Attention
          Background in search engines, and ideally hands-on experience with Apache Solr or Lucene
          Practical knowledge of NLP and search personalization techniques
          Experience building highly scalable systems powering a high-traffic consumer site
          Familiarity with building and deploying data pipelines and services in AWS
